    <!-- Rules screen -->
    <string name="rules_title">Rules</string>
    <string-array name="rules_rules">
        <item>The deck used in the game consists of 52 cards.</item>
        <item>Numbered cards count for as many points as their face value indicates.</item>
        <item>Kings, Jacks, Queens count for 10 points each.</item>
        <item>Aces count for 1 or 11 points (depends on what benefits the player more).</item>
        <item>The goal is to get as close to 21 points by drawing cards.</item>
        <item>If the player is dealt a card worth 10 points and an Ace they automatically end the round with a blackjack (the same applies to the dealer).</item>
        <item>Exceeding 21 points while drawing cards results in instant loss - the rule applies to both the dealer and the player.</item>
        <item>The round concludes with either the player or the dealer winning - the one that is closer to 21 points wins the hand.</item>
        <item>If the dealer and the player both have the same number of points the round results in a tie.</item>
        <item>If one of the participants exceeds 21 points the other one automatically wins the round.</item>
        <item>The game doesn\'t allow for splits or doubles - the betting only takes place at the beginning of the round, and the player is not allowed to split their hand.</item>
        <item>A bet must be worth at least 1/4th of the player\'s total amount chips.</item>
    </string-array>

